tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n33528"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَشَ (faraša) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"carpet, rug"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sheet, mattress, bedding"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"upholstery"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"furniture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a plain and soft tract of land","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pave"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to brush"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِرَاش (firāš)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فُرْشَة (furša)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of فُرْشَة (furša).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33528","headword_ar":"فَرْشٌ","root":"fr$","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of 1, q. v. passim. ―         -b2-  Also, used in the sense of a pass. part. n. in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is spread, of household furniture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) [such as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carpets"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mattresses"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaA$N","text_ar":"فِرَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seed-produce when it spreads itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) in [some of] the copies of the K, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA far~a$a","text_ar":"اـِذَا فَرَّشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the right reading, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*A furi$a","text_ar":"اذا فُرِشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to some, the word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seed-produce when it has become three-leaved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four-leaved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place abounding with plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spacious, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract of land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land that is plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even, and soft, and unobstructed by mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a depressed tract of land in which are trees of the kinds called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofuT","text_ar":"عُرْفُط"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salam","text_ar":"سَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which cause the mouths of the camels that eat them to become relaxed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) [Hence, app., the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlEaro$i A_ilaY Alfaro$i","text_ar":"مِنَ العَرْشِ اـِلَى الفَرْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From the highest sphere,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the empyrean, to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er$","text_ar":"عرش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collection"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a round plot"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloH","text_ar":"طَلْح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shrubs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small fire-wood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K.) ―         -b8-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Young camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young of camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, A, * K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariy$N","text_ar":"فَرِيشٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to have this meaning; but accord. to Aboo-Bekr, erroneously: (TA:) so the former signifies in the Kur vi. 143: (S, K:) Fr says, I have heard no pl. of it: and he adds, that it may here be an inf. n. used as a subst., from the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fara$ahaA A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"فَرَشَهَا ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faro$FA","text_ar":"فَرْشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bav~ahaA bav~FA","text_ar":"بَثَّهَا بَثًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": [see 1:] (S, TA:) but it is said in the K that in all of the above-mentioned senses that are assigned to it in that work, it has no sing.; meaning that it is used alike as sing. and pl.: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so accord. to some of the expositors of the Kur: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are fit for nothing but slaughter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) of camels, and of bulls or cows, and of sheep or goats; as some say: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is thrown down"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yufora$u","text_ar":"يُفْرَشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuloqaY","text_ar":"يُلْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for slaughter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the young of camels, and bulls or cows, and sheep or goats; used alike as sing. and pl.: (Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faro$u AlA_ibili","text_ar":"فَرْشُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","IAar","O","Lth","A","Mgh"]}]}}